---
isFront: true
---
<article class="front-promo">
  <!-- Section: Console -->
  <section id="promo-console" class="promo-console">
    <div class="container">
      <h2>Chatbot Hosting for <em>Developers</em></h2>
      <video autoplay loop>
        <source src="https://d3q6dk6wplpy9l.cloudfront.net/media/tty.mp4"
                type="video/mp4">
        Your browser does not support the video tag.
      </video>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Section: What you gets -->
  <section id="what-you-gets" class="what-you-gets">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="features">
        <div class="feature-item">
          <h3 class="feature-icon feature-backend-free">
            <i class="fa fa-gears" aria-hidden="true"></i>
          </h3>
          <h3>Backend Free</h3>
          <p>You build bot, we build backend.<br/>
            You need a robust backend as bot grows.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="feature-item">
          <h3 class="feature-icon feature-take-your-code">
            <i class="fa fa-code" aria-hidden="true"></i>
          </h3>
          <h3>Write your Bot</h3>
          <p>Write code, keep it yours.<br/>
            The chatbot core should always be yours.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="feature-item">
          <h3 class="feature-icon feature-monetization">
            <i class="fa fa-wifi" aria-hidden="true"></i>
          </h3>
          <h3>Omni-<wbr>channel</h3>
          <p>Write code once for our omni-channel interface.
            It works with many other messenger platforms.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="feature-item">
          <h3 class="feature-icon feature-take-your-code">
            <i class="fa fa-terminal" aria-hidden="true"></i>
          </h3>
          <h3>Developer toolchain</h3>
          <p>Don't leave a terminal to manage your chatbot.
            We gives you a CLI tool.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="features">
        <div class="feature-item">
          <h3 class="feature-icon feature-backend-free">
            <i class="fa fa-cubes" aria-hidden="true"></i>
          </h3>
          <h3>Elastic Container</h3>
          <p>We deploy your code on container. It scales along with a traffic.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="feature-item">
          <h3 class="feature-icon feature-backend-free">
            <i class="fa fa-database" aria-hidden="true"></i>
          </h3>
          <h3>Database</h3>
          <p>Key-value database is included in a plan.
            Store and use data with a simple method.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="feature-item">
          <h3 class="feature-icon feature-start-lean">
            <i class="fa fa-line-chart" aria-hidden="true"></i>
          </h3>
          <h3>Start lean</h3>
          <p>Start lean with zero cost.<br/>
            Pay as you go. We offers elastic pricing plans.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="feature-item">
          <h3 class="feature-icon feature-monetization">
            <i class="fa fa-bar-chart" aria-hidden="true"></i>
          </h3>
          <h3>Analytics</h3>
          <p>See that how users use your chatbot.</p>
        </div>
    </div>
    <%= link_to 'Learn more', '/docs/bothub-studio.html', :class => "btn" %>
  </section>

  <section id="code-example" class="code-example">
    <div class="container">
      <pre><code class="python">from bothub_client.bot import BaseBot
from bothub_client.messages import Message

class OrderBot(BaseBot):
   def handle_message(self, event, context):
       message = Message(event).set_text('Nice to meet you!')\
                               .add_quick_reply('Show menu')
       self.send_message(message)</code></pre>
      <div class="code-description">
        <p>Write a chatbot with BotHub.Studio SDK.</p>
        <p>You get a robust massive messaging, logging, analytic, database facilities with no additional efforts.</p>
        <p class="note">* For now, we supports python3 only. Python2, nodejs coming soon.</p>
        <p><%= link_to 'Learn more', '/docs/bothub-sdk-python.html', :class => "btn" %></p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Section: Supported channels -->
  <section id="channels" class="channels">
    <div class="container">
      <h2>Channels</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <img title="Facebook Messenber" src="https://cdn.worldvectorlogo.com/logos/facebook-messenger.svg"/>
